  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for opensc",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for opensc fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2024-8443: Fixed heap buffer overflow in OpenPGP driver when generating key (bsc#1230364)\n- CVE-2024-45620: Fixed incorrect handling of the length of buffers or files in pkcs15init (bsc#1230076)\n- CVE-2024-45619: Fixed incorrect handling length of buffers or files in libopensc (bsc#1230075)\n- CVE-2024-45618: Fixed uninitialized values after incorrect or missing checking return values of functions in pkcs15init (bsc#1230074)\n- CVE-2024-45617: Fixed uninitialized values after incorrect or missing checking return values of functions in libopensc (bsc#1230073)\n- CVE-2024-45616: Fixed uninitialized values after incorrect check or usage of APDU response values in libopensc (bsc#1230072)\n- CVE-2024-45615: Fixed uninitialized values in libopensc and pkcs15init (bsc#1230071)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
